Premier League chief executive Richard Scudamore and FA chairman Greg Dyke will fight to save England’s Christmas football programme when the World Cup moves to winter in Qatar in 2022.

But the plan now mooted by FIFA’s task force will wreck the global club calendar for years.

The most severely disrupted season for the English game will be the 2022-23 campaign, but it will not be the only one with fixtures shunted around. The 2021-22 and 2023-24 seasons will also be affected and some 50 other leagues will pay a price for FIFA’s discredited decision to award the world’s greatest tournament to a desert nation that is too hot to stage it in the summer. 

